'''''Star Wars Insider'' 27''' is the twenty-seventh issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in Fall [[1995]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Publisher"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Scoring the Trilogy]]" {{C|by [[Lukas Kendall]]}}
*"[[The Wonder Column|The New Wonder Column]]" {{C|by [[Anthony Daniels]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Around the World|''Star Wars'' Around the World]]"
*"[[LucasArts Update]]" &ndash; Excerpts from the Journal of a Rebel Pilot {{C|by [[Sue Seserman]]}}
*"[[Lucasfilm's Latest]]"
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" &ndash; A Guide to the Tales of the Jedi Universe, Part 2 {{C|by [[Bob Cooper]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; Droids, Ewoks, and the Mysterious Vlix (And the Truth about 4-L0M and Zuckuss!) {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"

===Features===
*"[[X-wings Sighted in Frankfurt]]" {{C|by [[Nelson Hall]]}}
*:<small>If you're traveling in Europe this winter and happen to notice an X-wing drive by, don't panic! You haven't traveled to a galaxy far, far away. FoxVideo International has built authentic, life-size X-wings to promote the new video Trilogy release and we have the ''Inside'' story from Lcuasfilm Archivist [[Nelson Hall]]!</small>
*"[[The Marketing of the Star Wars Video Trilogy|The Marketing of the ''Star Wars'' Video Trilogy]]" {{C|by [[Pamela Roller]]}}
*:<small>With a marketing blitz bigger than the Rebel assault on the Death Star, Twentieth Century Fox has been selling the magic of ''Star Wars'' to an eager, new global generation with the boxed set of the Trilogy that was recently released. We go behind the scenes at Fox to discover what went into this amazing campaign.</small>
*"[[Irvin Kershner: Renaissance Director]]" {{C|by [[Pete Hull]]}}
*:<small>An interview with the director of the [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|Empire Strikes Back]].</small>
*"[[A Star Wars CELibration|A ''Star Wars'' CELibration]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>A look back at the [[1985]]-[[1986]] Saturday morning series' Ewoks & Droids. Includes a complete episode guide for each.</small>
*"[[Return to Tatooine]]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Archaeologist Reynolds travels to [[Tunisia]] in April 1995, where they filmed [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']] and shares his story and photos.</small>
*"[[The Art of John Alvin Promises the Magic that Lucasfilm Movies Deliver]]" {{C|by Pamela Roller}}
*:<small>Interview with movie poster artist, John Alvin on the foreign VHS cover art he created.</small>

